  levelNumber: 27
  levelName: Tonina
  location: Chiapas, Mexico
  levelDescription: "From its towering acropolis, Tonin\xE1 carved power and legend
    into stone.\n\nTonin\xE1, located in the highlands of Chiapas, Mexico, was a
    powerful Maya city that flourished between 600\u2013900 AD. Its name means \u201CHouse
    of Stone\u201D, and it is renowned for its towering acropolis, which rises over
    70 meters, making it one of the tallest structures in Mesoamerica.\r\n\r\nTonin\xE1
    was a fierce rival of Palenque, and its monuments record victories in warfare,
    including the capture of Palenque\u2019s rulers. The site is notable for its
    hieroglyphic inscriptions, stucco reliefs, and carved monuments, which depict
    gods, warriors, and dynastic events.\r\n\r\nThe acropolis itself is a labyrinth
    of terraces, temples, and palaces, symbolizing both political power and spiritual
    authority. Archaeologists have also uncovered ballcourts, tombs, and evidence
    of Tonin\xE1\u2019s role as a regional capital."
  siteImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 65f2d76bc52374f419023f5df19fc846, type: 3}
